The function name of this problem called minimumNumber. It has two given values which are n and password. 
The solution must return the minimum number of characters that need to be added to make the password strong. 
To solve this, create a four groups of characters like numbers, owercase letters, uppercase letters, and 
special characters. Then, each character in password will be check to see if this character is belonged to 
one of those groups, and it will marked the password if it already had that type of character. After that, 
it will compare the number of missing types with the required password length of 6. And lastly, it will 
returned which value is greater.
